What is Object oriented programming(OOP)
    Its simply a way of writing code.some rules that we follow. there are other ways as well like functional
    programming. There are four main pillar of OOP 1)Inheritance 2)Polymorphism  3)Abstraction 4)Encapsulation.
Why should we learn OOP:
    1)Code re-usability
    2)Its easirer to write large amounts of code
    3)sharing code with others become easier
    4)Security of the code is increased
    5)Changing code becomes easier.
Object:
    An Object is something that we can physically touch. Everything around us like chairs, tables,
    computer etc. They are al objects. We can easily represent these objects inside
    our computers by telling a computer how an object looks like and how it behaves.
Class:
    A class is like a design/map/blueprint that we use to create objects.
String Class:
    A String class i used to store and manipulate text based data. Most of the information
    inside computer is processed in this form. String is most widely used class in all java.
Creating objects from String class.
    1)length() 2)isEmpty()